    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-05-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[Amends the Internal Revenue Code to include life insurance companies as an "includible corporation" for purposes of filing consolidated tax returns.<p>Permits an affiliated group which includes at least one domestic insurance company that elects to file a consolidated return rather than pay tax under certain life insurance provisions to use a phased-in percentage of insurance company net operating loss in determining its own taxable income. (Permits unused loss carryover.)<p>Provides for: (1) subsidiary stock basis adjustment; and (2) waiver of the five-year reconsolidation waiting period for certain formerly includible corporations which became nonincludible as a  result of becoming a subsidiary of a nonincludible life insurance company.]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to permit the consolidation of life insurance companies with other companies.</title>
